data.description: This charming 4-bedroom craftsman home is nestled on almost 2.5 acres along a creek. The double lot offers a private setting yet close to Walhalla and West Union. The home offers the perfect balance of comfort and style yet ample room with an open floor plan, expansive deck, and a basement as large as the main level living. As you enter you will notice the circular drive, stone-accented home, and a well-maintained yard. The owners have installed Zosia grass which has the yard looking green all summer long. The split plan has 2 guest rooms with a bath on the right side and the owner's suite on the left. The owner's ensuite has a large walk-in closet, double sinks, and a walk-in shower. The newly stained large deck overlooks the backyard and creek. The terrace level offers 2 large flex rooms that can be used as additional living space, an office, or a home gym, etc. There is also a 4th bedroom and bathroom with a large walk-in shower and a kitchenette.  The conscientious owners have carefully maintained this home so it is ready for the new owners to enjoy for years to come!  West Union is just outside of Walhalla and conveniently located to Seneca and Clemson University. Scatterwood Subdivision is just off Scenic Hwy 11 a few short miles from The Blue Ridge Mountains. Call for your personal showing today.
